The Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission seeks to recruit 41,940 temporary staff to buttress its capacity during the voter verification exercise.Temporary jobs will include 290 constituency ICT clerks, 1,450 register of voters verification assistants and 40,200 voter verification clerks. Each polling station will have one ICT clerk, one voter verification assistant per ward and one clerk per polling station for the voter verification. The electoral agency will also recruit 30 permanent county ICT staff, an elections coordinator for Kasarani constituency, and a constituency administrative assistant for Dadaab constituency. Eligible Kenyans have until April 14 to apply. The recruitment starts on May 10 or 30 days in every polling station across the country.